tk sự trùng hợp
balanced c. sự trùng hợp cân bằng
partial c. sự trùng hợp bộ phận

verb
-founds; -founded; -founding
[+ obj] to surprise and confuse (someone or something)
The strategy confounded our opponents.
The murder case has confounded investigators. - often used as (be) confounded
Investors were confounded by the conflicting reports.
to prove (someone or something) wrong
The school's team confounded all predictions and won the game.
The success of the show confounded critics.
informal + old-fashioned - used as an interjection to express anger or annoyance
Confound it! I can't find my keys!
